04/01/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Ali Ahmeti, leader of ethnic Albanian junior coalition partner Democratic Union for Integration, said on Monday (January 3rd) that there is no need for early elections, as the country faces more important issues. 
He also said it would be helpful if Washington were involved in resolving the name dispute with Greece, adding that both NATO and Brussels have proved to be very successful in resolving disputes worldwide. 
(Kanal 5, Sitel, Alsat M - 03/01/11)
